Alliance Soldier: Just sit and wait!
Tingko: Agh!
Tingko: Ow!!
Tindoiimu: Tingko! Are you okay!?
Jihasaha: Wait here, I'll deal with this!
Tingko: Please don't, we don't need more trouble. Please...
Jihasaha: ...Hmph, alright.
Tingko: Thank you. Heh, Jihasaha, you're so good to me~
Tingko: Princess, the soldiers say that there's no doubt Jiyanama is guilty, so she's been locked up somewhere else.
Tingko: They won't tell me any more than that.
Jihasaha: Figures. They don't have any evidence against the princess, so they won't put her in jail. Instead, they just lock us in some random house...
Tingko: You know they call these Ruined Cities? After the Alliance formed, all the tribes' original settlements were abandoned like this.
Tingko: So this one, Feihua City, used to be home to the Wind Sect. But now it's just used to host the Peace Ceremony, things like that...
Tindoiimu: It seems like this house was lived in by an old Wind Sect noble. But it's been 400 years... I wonder where he went...
???: Eh~ morning already?
Tindoiimu: A Satyr...?
???: Oh, please don't kill me! I've barely got any money!
Tingko: What pretty lanterns~
???: Pretty ain't it, eh? I sell these, but... take as many as you want! Just don't kill me...!
Tindoiimu: So all these lanterns and bags are all yours?
Tindoiimu: Are you a merchant?
Baa Baa: ...You mean... you're not thieves? Are you Alliance officials!?
Baa Baa: I'm sorry! I'm just here to sell some stuff, save up some cash!
Baa Baa: I reckon since no one's living out here anymore, I'd just crash for the night! I'm no squatter, real!
Baa Baa: Here, handmade thread from the Cat Tribe! Take it, a gift!
Baa Baa: Please don't confiscate my goods... I'd have bugger all left!
Jihasaha: Hmph, seems like she's no stranger to handing out bribes.
Tindoiimu: You're mistaken, we're not officers.
Baa Baa: Eh? Then who are ya'?
Tindoiimu: It's a long story... but it seems you're about as fond of the Alliance as we are.
Jihasaha: It makes sense that you'd want to do business during the ceremony, but... If you're a merchant, wouldn't the union provide you with lodging?
Baa Baa: Man, what's with the twenty questions?
Baa Baa: I'm just out on my own, I'm not part of the union~
Tingko: All of this stuff... you carry all this on your own?
Baa Baa: Yeah, it's nothin' really. Someone's gotta do it.
Baa Baa: Eh, who the heck are these guys?
Tindoiimu: What are you doing!?
Alliance Soldier: Listen here! Everyone except for the princess, get out!
Alliance Soldier: Now!
Baa Baa: Hey, I told you guys already to watch the goods! I've got to sell this stuff, you know!
Jihasaha: So, have the tribes come to a consensus?
Alliance Soldier: Arbiter Maeok said... the Insect Tribe conspired against General Yu... and the peace treaty has been annulled.
Tindoiimu: Annulled!?
Jihasaha: I knew it! I knew they'd use us as scapegoats!
Jihasaha: But we won't go down without a fight!
Alliance Soldier: Hey! Someone help!
Alliance Soldier: We've been ordered to take the princess hostage and exterminate all other maggots. Don't let her escape!
Jihasaha: Princess! The treaty—
Tindoiimu: ...I heard everything. Run!
Tindoiimu: (Whew... These guys are persistent!)
Jihasaha: Princess, I'll handle this.
Jihasaha: Run!
Tingko: Let me help, too!
Tindoiimu: No!
Alliance Soldier: They're over here!
Jihasaha: Run, Now!
Tingko: We're sorry to get you involved in this! Quick, go hide with the princess.
Baa Baa: Right!
Tindoiimu: (Jihasaha is everything to the Insect Tribe... If we lose him, then... then the tribe... my home...)
Tindoiimu: I have to go back!
Baa Baa: Hold on! Aren't you the princess!? You can't get yourself caught!
Tindoiimu: But leaving others to die just so I can live... what kind of princess would I be?
Baa Baa: Eh!? Come back!
Alliance Soldier: Sacrificing your own life for your cowardly princess—is it all worth it?
Jihasaha: If it means saving the Insect Tribe from the likes of you, and your corrupt Alliance, then yes.
Jihasaha: It's worth everything!
Alliance Soldier: I can't wait to squash you like the bugs you are. Kill em'!
Tindoiimu: Over here! I'm the one you want!
Alliance Soldier: It's the princess! Quick, grab her!
Tingko: Princess!
Tindoiimu: Stay where you are!
Tindoiimu: As princess of the Insect Tribe, I order you to bring news of our peace treaty's annulment back to the tribe! That is an order!
Jihasaha: Forgive me, but—
Tindoiimu: Jihasaha! You dare defy a direct order from your princess?
Tindoiimu: What if this information never makes it to the tribe? What if we end up getting slaughtered? You'll take responsibility?
Jihasaha: ...Your Highness... Very well, I will return with the news at once...
Tingko: No! Let me go! I want to be with the princess! Jihasaha!
Alliance Soldier: That maggot's getting away!
Alliance Soldier: After them!
Tindoiimu: Aren't I your target? What are you waiting for!?
Tindoiimu: (Jihasaha... Tingko... Please be okay.)
Tindoiimu: (The Insect Tribe must know the Alliance's true nature!)
